  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency NFI and Food Assistance to Displaced Households in Aleppo Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed intervention will address emergency humanitarian needs of newly displaced families through the provision of food and non-food item (NFI) assistance in Azaz district in northern Aleppo Governorate. Through the distribution of 2,170 food and 2,930 NFI kits, this approach seeks to meet the immediate food and nutrition needs of the most vulnerable while, at the same time, ensuring access to basic NFIs in order to provide a more comprehensive emergency response. Mercy Corps is already implementing similar activities in northern Syria with other funding and thus has considerable experience implementing activities within the Food Security and NFI/Shelter sectors. 

Mercy Corps pays particular attention to reaching households identified as the most vulnerable, including female and child headed households, people with disabilities, and the elderly, and uses community based targeting and accountability throughout the program. Mercy Corps will closely coordinate with other agencies active on the ground to avoid duplications and cover gaps.</narrative>
  </description>
